# WebFlux Rules

- Never use block(), blockOptional(), or join-like blocking in production code.
- Never call subscribe() in application flow code.
- Keep reactive chains readable; extract private methods instead of deep nesting.
- Prefer Mono/Flux end-to-end in reactive paths.
- Use onErrorResume/onErrorMap intentionally; do not swallow errors.
- Prefer timeout/retry only when explicitly justified.
- Avoid converting reactive code into imperative code just for convenience.
